Description:
Ave Maria, thank the heavens!
Providing all the certainty of a secure investment, this classical Victorian brick terrace ("Ave Maria," circa 1890s) offers an accessible launching pad into a tightly held neighbourhood. Enter via a verandah showcasing elegant wrought-iron work and discover an inviting hallway and 2 large bedrooms. The home then spectacularly opens up to reveal a light-filled living and dining room adjoining a functional kitchen. Step outside to a north-facing courtyard with laneway access and plenty of room for off-street parking. ?Offering instantly enjoyable living with further potential to update and add value, stroll to Smith and Gertrude Streets, Victoria Park Station and Abbotsford Convent with its enticing mix of restaurants and parkland. This is classic inner-city living with all the rewards!
* 2 large bedrooms
* Spacious living and dining room
* Functional kitchen
* Bathroom with bath and laundry capabilities
* Roomy courtyard with laneway access and capacity for off-street parking
* Stylish palm trees providing shade to north-facing courtyard
* Storage room running alongside house
* High ceilings and charming period flourishes throughout
* Gas heating
* Moments from Smith Street restaurants, Victoria Park Station, Eastern Freeway, parkland
Insights: 130 Keele Street, Collingwood VIC 3066 was last sold in 2016 and 29 other 2 bedroom house in Collingwood have recently been sold.

Description:
LOFTY LIVING IN THE THICK OF THE ACTION
The perfect complement to an exciting inner city lifestyle, this stunning two-storey warehouse conversion in the historic Foy & Gibson building offers the ultimate in New York style living amongst the boutiques, bars and eateries of the sought after Smith & Gertrude St precinct. Curved walls, a vast void & luxurious heated concrete floors set the tone for a ground floor boasting an expansive living space, 6m ceilings, modern kitchen, with an edgy ground floor bedroom. Take in incredible elevated views of the entire apartment from the mezzanine comprising a large loft-style robed bedroom, striking deco inspired central bathroom and light-filled retreat or home office with French windows opening to the iconic streetscape. This contemporary residence is perfectly positioned, walking distance to the CBD and only moments from transport. Enjoy the luxuries of intercom entry, secure off street parking, additional storage, spacious laundry and downstairs powder room.
Insights: 2/79 Oxford Street, Collingwood VIC 3066 was last sold in 2016 and 83 other 2 bedroom unit in Collingwood have recently been sold.

Description:
Industrial-style sanctuary
Dynamic inner city living is never more perfectly matched than with this smart and sophisticated ground floor warehouse apartment boasting the rarity not only of an open air courtyard but a street accessed private garage. Positioned in the heritage Foy & Gibson building in Collingwood's celebrated warehouse district, a dramatic double story wall of glass separates expansive outdoor courtyard spaces from a series of light filled living and entertaining domains served by an open plan stainless steel kitchen with smeg appliances. Arranged above, around a gallery like void, 3 bedrooms include 2 with fitted BIRs zoned to a fully tiled bathroom, the main in its own configuration with double ensuite, WIR and light filled sitting retreat (4th bedroom) with balcony. Cleverly designed for maximum natural light throughout with exposed original brickwork, reverse cycle heating/ cooling, hardwood timber floors and secure entry. Stroll to buzzing Smith, Gertrude and Brunswick Street's, trams and even the CBD.

Description:
Exceptional living, exclusive setting
Spacious design, secure surrounds and a profusion of natural light define the impressive credentials of this ground-floor apartment situated in a trendy city-edge neighbourhood with easy access to everything that counts. Impeccable interior showcases 2 bedrooms (large master) both with robes, stylish ensuite and main bathroom, open-plan living/dining area out to a wide north-facing courtyard with extensive paving and high fencing for extra privacy. Add to this a stone-top kitchen, split-system heating and cooling, European laundry, plus video intercom/secure entry and the bonus of two lower-level parking spaces. Stroll to Smith Street trams, cafe culture and renowned restaurants, easy access to Hoddle Street buses, Victoria Park Station and Eastern Freeway. Sensational city-edge lifestyle!

With an internal courtyard opening from the living area, this stunning home features split-system air conditioning, intercom, alarm system and quality inclusions.

Boutique Lifestyle / Perfect Investment
Defined by its quality renovations, distinctive floor-to-ceiling windows and an abundance of natural light, this first-floor apartment (1 of only 9) presents a ready-made environment of quality and privacy with the area's key lifestyle attractions all within easy reach. First-class modern living while retaining its cool retro charm, the apartment's stylish interior boasts one large bedroom (with robes) and deluxe ensuite bathroom, light-filled open lounge/dining area with elevated outlook. Add to this a contemporary stone-bench kitchen with soft-close drawers, tiled splashbacks and integrated fridge/freezer, as well as panel heating, internal laundry facilities, plus off-street parking space and intercom/secure entry. Close to cafes and restaurants, parks, vibrant shopping precincts, city-bound trams and trains, easy freeway access. City-edge quality and convenience - don't miss this one!

Description:
EASY-CARE LIVING AND UNSURPASSED LIFESTYLE ADVANTAGES
This sensational second-floor apartment is perfectly placed to enjoy the finest inner-city lifestyle attractions Melbourne has to offer, within walking distance to the vibrancy of Collingwood and Fitzroy nightspots, the culinary delights of famed Victoria St restaurants, and the sporting nirvana that is the MCG. Set well back from the street in the impressive 'Islington' complex, a relaxed style, elegant neutral palette and splendid leafy outlooks infuse the inviting interiors with an evident sense of comfort and warmth, incorporating a generous living and dining area, open kitchen boasting gas cooking, two double bedrooms with mirrored built-in robes and a sizeable bathroom that includes a Euro laundry, while the superb covered balcony provides effortless entertaining. A rewarding investment or owner-occupier haven, just moments to cafes, public transport and the CDB, this enticing residence also features reverse-cycle heating and cooling, intercom entry and a secure car space.

Description:
Spacious and light-filled, Seconds from Smith Street
Located on the top floor of this private block, with spanning northerly views down Oxford Street, this light filled two bedroom apartment offers the ultimate Collingwood lifestyle. Featuring two large bedrooms, both with built in robes and a generous sized central bathroom and European laundry.
A large open plan living and dining space accommodates for even the most esteemed of entertainers. An expansive kitchen boasting European appliances and stone-benchtops will no-doubt be wasted as you indulge night after night at the plethora of restaurants, wine bars and cafes making up the famous Smith and Gertrude Street precincts only minutes away.

You'll be spoilt for choice when it comes to public transport and the ability to walk to the various parks, boutiques and landmarks the area has to offer, not to mention only moments by foot to the heart of the CBD.
A unique opportunity to call the coveted Oxford Street precinct home, an inspection will not disappoint.

Description:

One of only nine, stylish, secure and orientated towards the northern sun, this great ground level apartment illustrates how to make a rewarding first move into an inner city setting. It's as simple as it is successful. A floor-plan of appealing character, enhanced by modern, low-maintenance surfaces, features a north facing living and dining area that incorporates an open plan kitchen zone where the proportions are pleasing and the presentation is exemplary. The bedroom, with built in robes and an ensuite bathroom, opens to a paved rear courtyard retreat complemented by a storage shed and separate off street parking on title, kept secure by automatic gate access. Victoria Park Station, Smith Street trams and a huge range of cafes and shopping options combine to confirm the convenience and the quality of the address.
Jason Sharpe : 0438 847 700
Insights: 2/13 Alexander Street, Collingwood VIC 3066 was last sold in 2016 and 49 other 1 bedroom unit in Collingwood have recently been sold.

Description:
Sensational city-edge warehouse living
Collingwood's iconic Foy & Gibson precinct sets the scene for this fabulous first-floor apartment that's sure to impress with its quality inclusions, abundance of natural light and enviable city-edge location. Chic interior comprises one large bedroom (with built-in robes) and stylish central bathroom, open-plan living/dining area and quality kitchen with Smeg cooking appliances and dishwasher. Other stand-out features include stone benchtops and polished concrete floors, European laundry, plus secure entry foyer and lower-level parking space. Industrial-styled modern living, Smith Street cafes and restaurants, shops and supermarkets, city-bound trams are all within walking distance. Exceptional living or blue-chip investing!

Description:
Massive price reduction, owner must sell!
Feel part of Collingwoods brewing history, as you make a grand entrance through the original faade of the James Hood and Co Malt House, and the large copper door, into the Silos development. Park your bike in the bike racks, and visit the gym, before heading up to the top floor of the warehouse apartments, where you will find this 2 bedroom apartment. Step directly into the open plan kitchen and living area with, island bench, timber floors, stone bench tops, ducted heating and cooling, and then directly onto the generous balcony, perfect, for relaxed weekend breakfasts. Not limited for storage the master bedroom includes a whole wall, of mirrored built in robes, and a little nook perfect for a desk or extra storage. A Euro laundry, with extra storage, and a stylish generous bathroom complete the apartments smart use of space, and design, however if you need it, a storage cage is located in the secure basement car park. A large covered decked area, with BBQ facilities and herb garden are there for the lucky residents in this small development, which fosters a community feel.
Islington Silos is conveniently located within a short walk to Smith Street, Brunswick Street and Melbourne CBD, giving you the amazing opportunity to wander down to your favourite, cafes, restaurants and iconic fashion stores. A stone's throw away from buses, trains and the Eastern Freeway this apartment is perfect for the owner occupier, or as a rental investment.
Insights: 208/55 Islington Street, Collingwood VIC 3066 was last sold in 2016 and 83 other 2 bedroom unit in Collingwood have recently been sold.
